04823nam a22008175i 9789048526253DE-B159720210824034702.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210824t20192019ne     fo  d z      eng d  a97890485262537 a10.1515/97890485262532doi  a(DE-B1597)545125  a(OCoLC)1130903212  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL 7aART0570002bisacsh1 aPitassio, Francesco, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aNeorealist Film Culture, 1945-1954 :bRome, Open Cinema /cFrancesco Pitassio. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2019] 4cÂ©2019  a1 online resource (384 p.) :b42  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aFilm Culture in Transition00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tAcknowledgements -- tIntroduction: An Uncertain Direction. Neorealist Cinema and Transitional Culture -- t1. Locating the Real -- t2. Lies of Memory -- t3. Looking at the Images -- t4. Actors, Non-professional Actors, Starlets, and Stars -- tBibliography -- tAbout the Author -- tName Index -- tFilm Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aUnique, truthful, brutal. Neorealism is often associated with adjectives stressing its peculiarities in representing the real, its lack of antecedents, and its legacy in terms of film style. While this is useful when confronting auteurs such as De Sica, Rossellini or Visconti, it becomes problematic when examining a widespread cultural practice that realistic modes deeply affected. This cultural production included filmmaking, literature, visual culture and photography, as well as media discourses. It was internally contradictory but fruitful inasmuch as its legacy influenced national culture for many decades to come. [-][-]The volume spotlights post-war Italian film culture by locating a series of crossroads, i.e. topics barely examined when discussing neorealism: nation, memory and trauma, visual culture, stardom, and performance. The aim is to deconstruct neorealism as a monument and to open up its cultural history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aPhilosophy. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aItalian Neorealism - Film Culture - Cultural History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048526253zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048526253423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048526253.jpg  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-073823-0  Art and Architecture eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb